CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 28, 1955, pg. 10, reads: "Mrs. Wynn Entertains - Mrs. Samuel J. Wynn, pictured center, entertained nearly a core of charming Pittsburgh dignitaries last Saturday at a dinner party held at her Iowa Street home. The occasion was a farewell affair honoring Miss Margaret G. Owen of the YWCA who retires soon.  Pictured clockwise are Miss Marion Dudley, who will take Miss Owen's place in 'Y' set-up; Mrs. Bryn J. Hovde, Miss Gloria Pace, Mrs. Moses Hazo, Mrs. W. S. Fitts, Miss Goldie Carter, Mrs. Nathaniel Dandridge, Mrs. Ray Brugler, Mrs. Wynn, Mrs. Robert Clark, Mrs. William M. Cuthbert, Mrs. Verne Wright, Mrs. Homer S. Brown, Miss Owen, Mrs. Thelma W. Allen, Mrs. Robert L. Vann and Mrs. Nathan Page. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Marion Dudley, Bryn J. Hovde, Gloria Pace, Mrs. Moses Hazo, Mrs. W. S. Fitts, Goldie Carter, Helen Dandridge, Mrs. Ray Brugler, Mrs. Samuel J. Wynn, Mrs. Robert Clark, Mrs. William M. Cuthbert, Mrs. Verne Wright, Wilhelmina Byrd Brown, Ms. Owen, Thelma W. Allen, Jessie Vann, and Mrs. Nathan Page, gathered around table for dinner party in Wynn home
